					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">How do old games like &quot;Link's Awakening&quot; or &quot;Final Fantasy Adventure&quot; do the collision check when the hero swings his sword in an arc? Especially the diagonal version.<br /><br />Usually, collision checks are done by declaring a rectangle for the object and seeing whether the rectangles would overlap.<br /><br />So, in a diagonal direction, do they simply put a rectangle over the whole sprite, so that a collision also registers even if the monster only touched empty space?<br />Or do they use various smaller rectangles, located diagonally along the sword, doing more than one collision check?<br />Or is there any other method?</div>

					
